git --version
git config --global user.name "{Enter Your Name}"
git config --global user.email "{Enter Your Email}"

git config --global user.email - [To Check Your Registered Email Id]

mkdir {FolderName} - To make a folder in your local device
cd {FolderName} - to go to Created Folder

git init - This code will setup an empty git respository 
git status - 
git add {files}
git status - 
git commit -m "{Initial Commit}"
git log - Show you your log as per you added in repo (On Master Branch OR -)

git status - Show the Info if you had made changes in file/code if you made changes - 

